                  <handDesc>
                     <!--ACHTUNG! first HandNote comes from writing system in Ethiospare. the others are one for each CHANGE OF HAND-->
                     <handNote xml:id="h1" script="Ethiopic">
                        <seg type="script">Fine, careful.</seg>
                        <seg type="ink">Black, red (vivid vermilion)</seg>
                        <date>18th century</date>
                        <seg type="rubrication">Nomina sacra; a few lines on the incipit page of
                           Texts II and III alternating with black lines; two initial lines of each
                           section of Texts I, II and III; elements of the punctuation signs;
                           elements of Ethiopic numerals; the word mǝʿrāf (e.g., fols. 84ra, 85vb,
                           90rb); days of the week: za-śälus (fol. 15r), za-ʿarb (fol. 53r),
                           za-ʾǝḥud (fol. 72r) in the margins.</seg>
                     </handNote>
                     <handNote xml:id="h2" script="Ethiopic">Hand a: 2r-95v. The handwriting remains
                        uniform throughout the Ms. and is characterized by finely shaped, slender
                        and upright
                        letters.<!--The names of this hands need to be replaced by appropriate refs.--></handNote>
                  </handDesc>
                  <additions>
                     <list>
                        <item xml:id="e1"><!--2019-04-02+02:00 Updated DD-002 
            from DomLib -->
                           <desc type="findingAid">- Daily readings are indicated with the names of the
                              days of the week written in the upper margin, encircled by dot lines:
                              zä-sänuy (e.g., fols. 2r, 3r, 78r), zä-śälus (e.g., fols. 15r, 16r,
                              79r), zä-rǝbuʿ (e.g., fols. 28r, 29r, 80r), zä-ḥamus (fols. 40r, 83r),
                              zä-ʿarb (<locus target="#53r">fol. 53r</locus>, 85r), zä-qädamit
                              (fols. 65r, 88r), zä-ʾǝḥud (fols. 72r, 90r).</desc>
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="e3"><!--2019-04-25+02:00 Updated ESdd002 
            from DomLib domlib_document_00001525-->
                           <desc>- One leaf originating form a 16th cent. Gospel manuscript (Mark 2:20 – 3:12) is used as a protective leaf on the front side. - The title of the work አርጋኖን is written in black paint on the front board and on <locus target="#1r">fol.  1r</locus>. - Fol. 1, used here as fly leaf, originates from a late 15th or early 16th-cent. Four Gospels book. Written in a careful, trained hand. - Rubricated name(s) of donor(s) erased from the supplication formulas: fols. 6ra, 6va, 15va, 29rb, 34ra, 35vb, 38rb, 58va, 64va-vb, 71ra, 77vb, 78ra, 79ra-va, 82r, 84vb, 85va, 86rb-va, 87rb, 88va-vb, 89va, 90ra, 93rb-vb, 94rb. - A word or phrase erased: <locus target="#10ra">fol.  10ra</locus>. - Corrections written interlineally or in the margins: fols. 6ra, 6va, 7vb, 21va, 47ra. - Amharic translations of some phrases, in a crude hand: fols. 22va, 25vb, 26va, 35ra-rb, 36rb, 92vb, 93rb.</desc>
                        </item>
                     </list>
                  </additions>
